Students take a lead role in the annual meeting of Zhejiang University, research results make people’s minds open - Xinhua English.news.cn
Wash your hands with air, judge the disease with a breath, and accurately search for the source of the haze. Last night, at the opening ceremony of the 2016 Academic Annual Conference of Zhejiang University, a series of thought-provoking academic achievements were honored.
The main researchers of these achievements are students, and their research has covered various fields including the environment, machinery, energy, medical care, life sciences, humanities education and so on. The students started from a curious idea and created many high-end inventions with application value, some of which have won awards at domestic and international level.
Biosensors: Your home health checker
Zhang Diming, a doctoral student from the School of Biomedical Engineering, and his team demonstrated a smartphone-side biosensor, half the size of a smartphone.
"You only need to take a breath, and this instrument can initially detect your health status from the composition of the gas you exhale."
Zhang Diming said that this set of sensors is connected to the smartphone and that after exhaling air, the health report will be displayed on the phone.
Smart bracelets on the market that can detect health status generally detect physical parameters such as temperature and pulse.
This biosensor uses graphene, a new type of material, which targets chemical elements, and its keen “smell” enables it to more deeply and accurately reflect the health of the body.
Smart Surgery Lights: The Doctor's High-Energy Eyes
In addition to smartphones, smart surgical lights are also used in operating rooms.
This invention won a silver medal at the 44th International Exhibition of Inventions in Geneva, Switzerland this year.
The team of master students Zhu Linjing and Shen Junfei from the School of Optoelectronic Science and Engineering opened up new ideas in the shortcomings of traditional surgical lights and invented the intelligent LED surgical shadowless lamp.
"The early detection and incomplete removal of many diseases are related to the lights that doctors use in operating rooms."
Shen Junfei said, for example, during early cancer examination, if doctors fail to identify all tumor tissue in time, the cancer cells will spread later.
This smart surgical light has four light disks that can enhance the differentiation of different tissues under illumination by adjusting the spectrum.
During the operation, doctors can adjust the spot size, brightness, spectrum, color uniformity and shadow-less rate at any time according to surgical needs and personal habits.
This intelligent surgical light has been tested in hospitals such as Run Run Shaw Hospital Affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine and Children's Hospital Affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine, and has received good feedback.
Last October, the invention won first prize in the National Challenge Cup.
Washing hands with air: water saving and cool
Ordinary people wash their hands by using water and at the most wipe some soap and squeeze some hand sanitizer, while Li Qizhang and other students have created an “air hand washing device”.
Once we stand on the provided sink, the air will be compressed by our body weight.
"It's like a pump.
The compressed air forms a fluid at the tap and combines with the water.
} This way, we can wash our hands clean!”
Color reaction and bacterial residue experiments prove that the effect of washing hands by this method is the same as that of ordinary handwashing.
This device only needs to rely on our own gravity as the driving force, which can not only ensure the degree of cleaning, but also save 90% of water. The whole process has no energy consumption at all, and is energy-saving and environmentally friendly.
Last year, at the second Global Grand Challenge Summit, this invention stood out among the world's top universities and won the only gold award.
Chongqing vocational school pilots modern apprenticeship system, admitting employees for prospective enterprises - Xinhua English.news.cn
Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that starting this year, our city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship" talent training model in 60 secondary vocational schools. Students who receive the training will have apprenticeship status. After they are enrolled, the pilot enterprises will pre-record them as employees of their units.
The Municipal Education Commission has called for standardizing the recruitment, admissions and employer employment procedure of secondary vocational schools, clarifying the dual identities of the students in secondary vocational schools and prospective employees of enterprises. According to the principle of two-way selection, the apprentices, schools and enterprise must sign a tripartite agreement. For apprentices who reach the age of 16 but not 18, there are four parties which must sign an agreement, such as apprentices, guardians, schools and enterprises, to define the rights and interests of each party and the specific positions, teaching content, rights and interests guaranteed for the on-the-job training.
Pilot schools are encouraged to use the modern apprenticeship system to carry out pre-job training and job-transfer training for employees in cooperation with cooperative enterprises.
Pilot schools need to reform their talent training models.
Schools and enterprises jointly design talent training plans and formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, job standards, enterprise master standards, quality control standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot program takes the training schooling system as a pilot period. The internship time of students in the company is determined according to the professional personnel training program and the post-internship is generally 6 months.
In enterprise practice, a team-based management mode should be implemented. According to the characteristics of different majors, one master can lead 2 to 5 apprentices to form study groups to ensure that students master the skills required for each rotation position.
According to the arrangement, from 2016 to August 2019, our city has decided to establish 60 municipal secondary vocational modern apprenticeship pilot programs in three batches. Each pilot program is about 50 people, training a total of about 3000 students (apprentices).
Following the principle of first piloting and then implementing and gradually advancing from point to area, we will explore and establish a long-term mechanism for joint enrollment, joint training, and integrated education between schools and companies so as to effectively improve students’ job skills and increase their counterparts’ employment rate and employment quality.
