Don't scare people at the starting line - Xinhua English.news.cn
When visiting the book market, you can often feel the popularity of successful study books.
Many of today's success books promote “best practices” – first assuming or implying that you can “do it” and then tell you the “what” of what needs to be done.
It amounts to saying that we have skipped over "how to do it?" the most important and fundamental part.
Precisely for this reason, these books have one thing in common – either do it as best as you can or do nothing at all, either a 100 or a 0; you either climb Mount Tai or you simply stay put.
This "best principle" can be admitted to "extremely correct" by anyone who looks at it, but 99% of the people will be frightened at the starting line.
Because this theory advocates a path of “you must make up your mind, become a new person, and make a 180-degree transition”, which happens to be the fatal weakness of many people.
To someone who sticks to the rules, follows convention and refuse to change, you have to shout "you want to change" in his ear. This is undoubtedly a deceitful act of deceiving oneself and others.
Most people would be timid in front of the word “change”, hold back and they have a difficulty in making up their minds. Or they will use a sudden impulse to make the decision to “change”, and take the first step courageously. But it is usually a short-lived situation. After a while, they fail, and it is hard to see continuity.
Mr Ma Sanli's famous cross talk "Starting from Tomorrow" is the classic that expresses this "universal human nature" most vividly.
The biggest problem with the “best principle” is that the threshold is too high, often exceeding the limitations of ordinary people’s ability, making most people "sigh with awe."
Perhaps the “second-best principle” is an approach that may put more ordinary people on a path to relative success.
The core of “The Next Best Principle” is to “lower the threshold” - what it encourages is a kind of “small wins makes for big wins” theory, that is, if you cannot do 100, just do 1: because 1 is always greater than 0; if you don’t get to Mount Tai, you can just climb the small sand dunes at your doorstep, because that is always better than standing still.
In short, as long as you do something, it is better than nothing.
Since the threshold has been greatly reduced, there are more chances for ordinary people to persevere, and as long as one persists in everything, the probability of success will also increase.
It’s just that the road to success following the 'second best principle’ is a bit longer.
All in all, although the "best principle" is ostensibly under the banner of enabling all the people to succeed, ultimately it can actually inspire only a few, while the "second best principle" can effectively motivate more people and benefit as many people as possible.
The resource reserve of naked carp in Qinghai Lake increases by 7,100 tonnes this year - Xinhua English.news.cn
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, December 11 (Reporters Luo Xiaofei and Zhang Hongxiang) The reporter learned from the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs that the latest monitoring results show that the reserve of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake has increased by 7,100 tons this year compared with the previous year to 108,500 tons. Compared with the initial protection period in 2002, the cumulative increase was more than 40 times.
The common name of Qinghai Lake naked carp is "Huangyu", which is a unique and precious species of fish in Qinghai Lake. It plays a pivotal role in maintaining the security of the "water - fish - bird" ecological chain and biodiversity in the Qinghai Lake Basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, due to human-made mass killings and the increasingly degraded aquatic environments for breeding naked carp, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake decreased sharply. In 2002, the resource reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake was only 2,592 tons.
In 2004, the Qinghai Lake naked carp was listed as an endangered species in the “Red List of China’s Species”.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has implemented the closure of lakes for fish breeding, prohibited any unit, collective or individual from fishing for naked carp on Qinghai Lake and the main rivers and tributaries of the lake area, and prohibited the sale of naked carp and its products.
At the same time, through measures such as artificial proliferation and release, cleaning up the main rivers leading to Qinghai Lake water, and designing scientific and reasonable "fish passages", the protection effort has been continuously strengthened, and the reserves of naked carp in Qinghai Lake are increasing year by year.
Yang Lin, deputy director of the Qinghai Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, said that up to now, nearly 180 million naked carp have been artificially proliferated and released in Qinghai Lake, and the contribution rate to the recovery of the Qinghai Lake naked carp resource exceeds 23 percent.
The Three River Source region in Qinghai is an important ecological barrier and water conservation area in China and even Asia, while Qinghai Lake is a natural barrier and ecological functional area controlling the eastward spread of desertification in the west.
In order to protect the ecological environment of the Three River Headwaters and Qinghai Lake waters, protect aquatic wildlife and maintain biodiversity on the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has recently issued announcements of ban on fishing in key waters of Yangtze River, Yellow River and Qinghai Lake since this year, and has set up a comprehensive management system of “one river, one river and one lake”.
